               <msContents>
                  <summary>Shorthand manual with the commentary: series of entries, each with four words (a tetrad) and a large shorthand sign surrounded by 4 small signs in the margin</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Written along the fibers; on the other side a documentary text, P.Col. VIII 222, dated 160-161 AD</note>
                     <note type="general">On the front 17 + 20 lines of writing in 2 cols. by a large, round book hand</note>
                     <note type="general">Entries separated by paragraphoi; there are a few stops within each entry</note>
                     <note type="general">Entries 2-13 of the papyrus seem to correspond to Milne (Greek Shorthand Manuals) tetrads 82-85, 88-92, 95-97 and in some instances supplement Milne</note>
                     <note type="general">it provides evidence for a "standard" version of the commentary</note>
                     <note type="general">There are a few phonetic mistakes</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">In Greek</textLang>
                  </msItemStruct>
